  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Deseed the<strong> pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>and peel and finely chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650382666405-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650382666405-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650382666405-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650382666405-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650382666405-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and 10g <span class=\"text-danger\">[20g]</span> <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>, <strong>diced carrot</strong>, <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>,<strong> sliced pepper</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the<strong> garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>star anise</strong> and cook for 8-10 min, or until the onion has started to soften and the tomatoes have broken down</p><p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650382676294-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650382676294-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650382676294-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650382676294-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650382676294-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are cooking, combine the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>ground turmeric</strong> (save the rest for later!) with 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>turmeric stock</strong></p><p>Once the vegetables have softened, add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring continuously</p><p>Add the <strong>turmeric stock</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook for 5-6 min or until reduced by half</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1650382687238-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1650382687238-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1650382687238-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1650382687238-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1650382687238-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>remaining ground turmeric</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and stir until you have a smooth paste</p><p>Add the <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>white wine vinegar</strong></p><p>Whisk in a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>with a pinch of<strong> black pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>sunny aioli</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1650382699619-x200.jpg",
